        <abstract> 
<p>Describes his recent work on <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> digestion of organic materials, e.g., albumen and gelatin. Edward Frankland has given CD a rough test for pepsin. Some plant extracts cause as much inflection as meat. Has found some reversible inflection with heat and perhaps some heat rigor. Has measured the extreme sensitivity of <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> with very dilute solution of ammonium phosphate.</p> 
        </abstract>
